#: inc/Engine/Abilities/Options/GetOptions.php:42
msgid "Get WP Rocket options"
msgstr ""

#: inc/Engine/Abilities/Options/GetOptions.php:43
msgctxt "Ability description"
msgid ""
"Retrieves current WP Rocket settings as a flat key-value object, including toggles and array-type options.\n"
"Use this when the user asks what is enabled, disabled, or excluded. Do not use it to change settings; use set-option instead.\n"
"Always call this before set-option when changing an array-type option, to avoid overwriting existing values. Do not show internal, credential, or read-only keys to the user.\n"
"Unless the user asks for another format, present settings as a grouped dashboard with cards for Caching, File Optimisation, Media, CDN, Database, and Heartbeat. Each card should show a group-level badge, setting rows, status pills, impact bars, and plain-language descriptions using the approved colors."
msgstr ""

#: inc/Engine/Abilities/Options/SetOption.php:135
msgid "Set a WP Rocket option"
msgstr ""

#: inc/Engine/Abilities/Options/SetOption.php:136
msgctxt "Ability description"
msgid ""
"Writes one WP Rocket option using option_name and option_value. update_mode defaults to update, which appends to arrays; use replace to overwrite a full array.\n"
"Use this when the user wants to enable, disable, or update a specific setting. For array-type options, always call get-options first.\n"
"Confirmation is required before calling. First show the setting name and the current value to new value. Then ask: `Confirm this change?` and wait for a clear yes or no.\n"
"A user request such as `enable it` or `disable it` is not enough confirmation. Only call this ability after the user gives an affirmative answer in the same turn."
msgstr ""

